
Assembly trampolines for the two SecTrustSettingsCopy* wrappers restored in the
companion security.go patch (they are address-taken from Go code). These are the
standard NOSPLIT JMP stubs upstream Go uses for every such wrapper; the pair
below is byte-for-byte Go's own code from Go 1.24, removed in Go 1.26 alongside
the wrappers. Compare against the upstream source:

  https://github.com/golang/go/blob/go1.24.13/src/crypto/x509/internal/macos/security.s

--- src/crypto/x509/internal/macos/security.s.orig	2026-05-29 11:26:39.000000000 -0400
+++ src/crypto/x509/internal/macos/security.s
@@ -25,3 +25,7 @@
 	JMP x509_SecCertificateCopyData(SB)
 TEXT ·x509_SecTrustCopyCertificateChain_trampoline(SB),NOSPLIT,$0-0
 	JMP x509_SecTrustCopyCertificateChain(SB)
+TEXT ·x509_SecTrustSettingsCopyCertificates_trampoline(SB),NOSPLIT,$0-0
+	JMP x509_SecTrustSettingsCopyCertificates(SB)
+TEXT ·x509_SecTrustSettingsCopyTrustSettings_trampoline(SB),NOSPLIT,$0-0
+	JMP x509_SecTrustSettingsCopyTrustSettings(SB)
